      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The curtain crashed down on another Toronto Maple Leafs season - a grim 32-36-14 slog that left them <strong>8th in the Atlantic, 31 games back with just 78 points and a seven-game losing skid to cap the misery</strong>. No playoffs, no miracles, just the cold math of 15th in the East, eliminated long before the final buzzer. The core - Matthews, Marner, Tavares - carried the load again, but the blue line crumbled under pressure, goaltending faltered, and depth scoring evaporated like morning dew on the Gardens' ice. Whispers of coaching upheaval swirl around Sheldon Keefe's future; the suits upstairs must decide if another summer shuffle patches the leaks or demands a deeper gutting. Free agency looms with cap space tight, and that draft lottery ping-pong ball could gift a franchise cornerstone. <strong>Watch the top-10 pick odds - it's the lone lottery ticket left in this rebuild-or-retool riddle</strong>. Toronto's faithful deserve better than perennial also-rans; the reset button blinks urgently.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
      },
