      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Another Arizona sunset swallowed the Blue Jays whole - <strong>Corbin Carroll's eighth-inning grand slam off Jeff Hoffman turning a tense tie into a 6-2 gut punch</strong>, capping their fourth straight loss and dropping them to 7-13, dead last in the AL East, 5 games back. They stranded runners like lost tourists, scratching out just two runs on 12 hits while Hoffman, who'd been mowing down hitters with 18 K's in under nine innings this year, watched his bases-loaded nightmare sail to left-center. Kazuma Okamoto's bat stayed quiet in the clutch, and the pitching staff's early-season cracks widened into canyons on this desert road trip, swept by the Brewers before the D-backs piled on. No fresh injuries reported, but the lineup's punchless funk - now a four-game skid - screams urgency for a lineup shakeup before the ghosts of contention fade entirely. <strong>Kevin Gausman takes the hill this afternoon in the rubber game at Chase Field - win or sink deeper into April irrelevance</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
      },
