      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft smoke thickens around Washington, where a 5-12 stumble left them third in the NFC East - six games back, staring down a No. 7 pick that screams rebuild. Dan Quinn's crew, armed with a second first-rounder from Dallas, eyes the trenches and skill weapons to prop up Jayden Daniels after a barren '25 cupboard. <strong>CBS's Carter Bahns lit up the weekend mock circuit, forecasting a juicy trade-back with the Cowboys - sliding to 12 for Biletnikoff winner Makai Lemon, then snagging corner Jermod McCoy at 20</strong>, turning rivals' picks into Dan Quinn's bounty. Free agency bled talent - Deebo Samuel, Austin Ekler, Von Miller, Zach Ertz all hitting the market - leaving wideout and edge as glaring holes, with mocks piling on WR Lemon, CB McCoy, safety Bud Clark, and QB Taylen Green in later rounds. Terry McLaurin's the lone holdover stud, but Daniels needs ammo now. The front office flirts with trading down for volume - per Chat Sports' perfect seven-round haul - yet NFC East vultures like Philly root for their folly. <strong>With the draft ticking down next week, watch if Quinn pulls the trigger on that Cowboys swap - it's the pivot from pretender to contender</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
